=== Etymology ===
From the Old English ''[[nawiht]]'' "no whit"
=== Noun ===
'''naught''' ''or'' '''nought'''
# [[zero]]
#: ''Yet another '''naught''' on the scoreboard for the home team.'''
# [[nothing]]; [[nothingness]]
#: ''[[Naught]] good can come of this, you mark my words.''

